CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, National Edition, July 4, 1942, pg. 13, reads: "Courier 'Double V' Girl of the Week - Lovely Vivian Redd, of Cleveland, Ohio, is the current selection to wear the honor of 'Courier 'Double V' Girl of the Week.' Miss Redd, recent visitor to Pittsburgh, makes a beautiful picture as she poses beside a lily pond in Smoky City's Schenley Park.  She is an enthusiastic booster of the The Courier in her home city and is employed as a salesgirl in a popular music store. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Pittsburgh Courier "Double V girl" Vivian Redd posed in front of lily pond in Schenley Park, Oakland
